other_tests.procedure_name: Endoscopic insertion of stent (tube) into bile duct
other_tests.findings: Stent was placed; CBD stone not found.

findings.LIVER: Normal hepatic parenchyma; 0.8 x 0.7 x 0.7 left liver cyst; no focal liver mass.
findings.BILE DUCTS: No intrahepatic biliary dilation; CBD measures 3 mm.
findings.GALLBLADDER: Layering sludge and gallstones; mildly distended gallbladder; thickened edematous wall measuring 5 mm; small amount of pericholecystic free fluid.
findings.PANCREAS: Normal, without masses or pancreatic ductal dilation.
findings.KIDNEYS: Right kidney 10.6 cm; left kidney 10.2 cm; normal echogenicity with multiple bilateral parapelvic cysts; no masses, stones, or hydronephrosis.
